4. Sharing with Authorized Partners: Some of our services will be provided by authorized partners only for the purpose stated in this Policy. We may share some of your personal information with our partners to provide better customer service and user experience. We will only share your personal information for lawful, legitimate, necessary, specific and explicit purposes, and will only share the personal information necessary for the provision of services, ensuring compliance with the principle of minimization. Our partners have no right to use the shared personal information for any other purpose. Currently, our licensing partners include the following types:
1) Authorized partners of advertising and analysis services. Unless we get your permission, we will not share your sensitive personal information with partners who provide advertising and analysis services. We may provide anonymized information to these partners for advertising operations analysis. Anonymity ensures that the information does not identify you personally.
2) Suppliers and service providers. We may send the information to suppliers and service providers that support our business, such as payment service providers and logistics service providers, to provide you with transaction services and postal services.
3) Joint operation partners. When the game is co-operated, we may share your information with our co-operated partners to support customer support or operational activities such as tracking and processing of customer service feedback problems, financial reconciliation and so on.
5. For companies, organizations and individuals with whom we share personal information, we will sign strict confidentiality agreements with them and require them to handle personal information in accordance with our instructions, this Privacy Policy and any other relevant confidentiality and security measures.
(2) Assignment
We will not transfer your personal information to any company, organization or individual other than Shenzhen Palm Leyou Technology Co., LTD., except for the following:
1. Transfer with express consent: After obtaining your express consent, we will transfer your personal information to other parties;
2. In the case of merger, acquisition, sale of business segment, bankruptcy and liquidation, if the transfer of personal information is involved, we will require the new company or organization holding your personal information to continue to be bound by this privacy policy. If the scope of personal information collection or the purpose of use is changed, we will require the company or organization to seek authorization from you again.
(3) Public disclosure
We will only publicly disclose your personal information if:
1. After obtaining your explicit consent;
2. Disclosure based on law: We may publicly disclose your personal information in the case of laws, legal procedures, lawsuits, government supervision or mandatory requirements of government authorities.
(4) Storage
1. Location of Personal Information Storage: We guarantee that personal information collected and generated by us in the People's Republic of China will be stored in the People's Republic of China. We will not transfer your personal information out of the country without your express authorization, the explicit provisions of laws and regulations, and/or the requirements of relevant authorities. We will store your information in a secure way, including local storage (using APP for data caching), database and server logs.
2. Storage Term of Personal Information: We guarantee that we will only store your personal information within the period necessary to realize the purpose of the service or under the conditions and term stipulated by laws and regulations. After the above storage period, we will delete or anonymize your personal information. However, unless you exercise the right to delete or cancel the account, or otherwise stipulated by laws and regulations (for example, according to the E-commerce Law, the commodity and service information and transaction information shall be kept for no less than three years from the date of transaction completion).
How do we protect your personal information
(a) We have adopted industry-standard security measures to protect the personal information you provide from unauthorized access, public disclosure, use, modification, damage or loss. We will take all reasonably practicable steps to protect your personal information. For example, the HTTPS protocol is used to encrypt and protect network communications. Based on the operation and maintenance audit and access control of the Bastion machine, firewalls, WAF (Web application firewall), and anti-ddos traffic cleaning devices are deployed at the network border. Sensitive data is protected by asymmetric communication encryption and strict access control in the database. An in-depth security defense system is deployed on the network and terminal layer of the server to prevent malicious attacks. A complete information security management system has been established to regulate the daily activities of internal personnel on data access, use, editing, storage, sharing and deletion, ensuring that only authorized personnel can access the protected information; Life-cycle monitoring and early warning of access, storage and use of sensitive data; Manage background default masking and access authorization and audit control; And we will organize information security and privacy protection training courses and awareness education related activities to enhance staff's awareness of the importance of protecting personal information.
(2) Our data security capabilities: application layer encryption, network layer encryption, database encryption, network access anomaly monitoring, database access anomaly monitoring, etc.
(c) We will take all reasonably practicable steps to ensure that we do not collect irrelevant personal information. We will only retain your personal information for the shortest period necessary to achieve the purpose stated in the Cost Policy, unless it is necessary to extend the retention period or is permitted by law.
(4) The Internet is not an absolutely secure environment. We strongly recommend that you avoid sending personal information through non-encrypted means as much as possible. Please help us keep your account secure by using a complex password (including numbers, upper and lower case letters, special symbols, and avoiding names, birthdays, etc.).
(V) We will regularly update and make public the relevant contents of security risk, personal information security impact assessment and other reports.
(6) The Internet environment is not 100% safe, we will try our best to ensure or guarantee the security of any information you send to us. If our physical, technical, or management protection facilities are damaged, which leads to unauthorized access, public disclosure, tampering, or destruction of information, resulting in damage to your legitimate rights and interests, we will assume the corresponding legal liabilities.
(VII) In the event of an unfortunate personal information security incident, we will, in accordance with the requirements of laws and regulations, timely inform you of the basic situation and possible impact of the security incident, the disposal measures we have taken or will take, suggestions you can independently prevent and reduce risks, and remedial measures for you. We will timely inform you of the relevant situation of the event by letter, short message, phone call, push notification and other means. If it is difficult to inform the subject of personal information one by one, we will release the announcement in a reasonable and effective way. At the same time, we will also in accordance with the requirements of the regulatory authorities, take the initiative to report the disposal of personal information security incidents.
Your Rights
In accordance with relevant laws, regulations and standards of China, we guarantee that you exercise the following rights regarding your personal information:
1. You may request us to delete your personal information under any of the following circumstances:
1) If our handling of personal information violates laws and regulations;
2) If we collect and use your personal information without your consent;
3) If our handling of personal information violates our agreement with you;
4) If you no longer use our products or services, or you have logged out of your account;
5) If we no longer provide you with products or services.
2. If we decide to respond to your removal request, we will also notify the entities from whom we obtained your personal information and request them to delete it in a timely manner, unless otherwise required by laws and regulations, or these entities are independently authorized by you.
3. After you delete the information from our service, we may not delete the corresponding information from the backup system immediately due to the limitation of system operation, but we will delete the information during the backup update.
(3) Change the scope of your authorization
1. The collection of user information shall follow the principle of necessity, and some basic personal information is required to provide basic game service functions (see Article 1 of this Policy). You may give or withdraw your authorization consent for the collection and use of non-essential parts of your personal information at any time.
2. You can contact us by email to make your request.
3. After you revoke your consent, we will no longer process the corresponding personal information. However, your decision to withdraw consent will not affect the processing of personal information that was previously carried out based on your authorization.
4. If you do not want to accept the SMS commercial advertisements we send to you, you can follow the unsubscribe guidelines attached with the advertising content at any time.
(5) The personal information subject cancels the account
1. If you are a user of the combined transport channel of the game and your game-related accounts are managed and operated by the combined transport channel, you can apply for account cancellation according to the account cancellation channel provided by the combined transport channel.
2. If you use the associated wechat or QQ account as the game account to log in to the relevant game, you need to log out of the wechat or QQ account. Please log out of the wechat or QQ account according to their instructions.
3. After the account is closed, we will stop providing you with products or services and delete your personal information at your request, unless otherwise stipulated by laws and regulations.
(6) Personal information The subject shall obtain a copy of personal information
1. You have the right to obtain a copy of your personal information. You can contact us via email and we will reply to your request within 15 working days. Get our contact information, including service hotline, self-service, online customer service, etc., and contact us with your request.
(7) Constraint information system automatic decision-making
1. The automatic decision-making function of information system has not been used yet. In the future, if in some business functions we use a mechanism to make decisions based solely on non-human automatic decision making mechanisms such as information systems, algorithms, etc., we will provide you with the option to turn off automatic decision making.
(8) To respond to your above request
1. For security purposes, you may be required to provide a written request or otherwise prove your identity. We may ask you to verify your identity before we process your request.
2. We will reply you within 15 working days. If it is not possible to give a reply within such period due to objective reasons, we will contact you in advance to extend the reply period to give you a satisfactory reply.
3, for your reasonable request, we do not charge in principle, but for repeated requests, beyond the reasonable limit, we will charge a certain cost according to the situation. We may reject requests that are gratuitously repetitive, require excessive technical means (e.g., require the development of new systems or a fundamental change in existing practices), pose a risk to the legal rights of others, or are highly impractical.
4. We will not be able to respond to your request under the following circumstances:
1) Those related to the personal information controller's performance of obligations stipulated by laws and regulations;
2) Those directly related to national security and national defense security;
3) those directly related to public safety, public health or major public interests;
4) Those directly related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgment;
5) The personal information controller has sufficient evidence to show that the personal information subject has subjective malice or abuse of rights;
6) To protect the major legitimate rights and interests of the personal information subject or other individuals, such as life and property, but it is difficult to get the consent of the person;
7) Responding to the request of the personal information subject will cause serious damage to the legitimate rights and interests of the personal information subject or other individuals and organizations;
8) Those involving trade secrets.
How do we handle children's personal information
(1) We attach great importance to the protection of children's personal information. In accordance with relevant laws and regulations of the state, we regard any minor under the age of 14 as a child. Mainly for adults. Without the consent of the parents or guardian, children should not create your own personal account, for the approval of the parents and children's personal information collection, we will only be allowed by law, and provide necessary, parents or guardians explicit consent or necessary to protect the child under the condition of use or disclose this information.
(1) We will protect the legitimate rights and interests of minors (including children) through the use of the anti-addiction system in accordance with the national anti-addiction policy. We will determine whether the real name information of the relevant account is a minor through the verification of the real name identity and other information, and then decide whether to include the account into the anti-addiction system.
(2) The scope of our collection, sharing, transfer and public disclosure of children's personal information shall be the same as the above service scope, but any collection, storage, sharing, transfer and public disclosure of children's personal information shall be subject to the express consent of the children's guardian in advance. If national laws and regulations on the protection of children's personal information issue new policies to restrict activities related to children's personal information, we will accordingly adjust the scope of collection, sharing, transfer and public disclosure of children's personal information provided by us in accordance with national laws and regulations.
(c) If you are the legal guardian of the child, please pay attention to whether the child in your custody is using the service or providing his personal information after obtaining your authorized consent. If the child's guardian explicitly refuses us to provide services to the child in the above way, we will promptly delete the personal information of the child collected, stored and used by us and stop providing services to the child in accordance with the law.
(4) The personal information of children we collect is defined as sensitive information, and all the personal information of children we collect is stored in mainland China. To ensure information security, we take measures such as encryption to store children's personal information. Children's personal information is protected by strict technical safeguards. For example, we desensitize children's personal information after it is collected. In addition, a strict data security management process has been established, and the access and use of sensitive data are strictly restricted. All access or permission applications for sensitive information need to be applied for, approved, and kept records.
